<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-11T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-11T21:00:00-05:00" n="435" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d435">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.7962/46: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-11T22:00:00-04:00">March 11,
                                    1942—10 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>48. Your 44, February 25, 11 a.m. For McBride. Details of the credit plan
                            are being worked out and should be available shortly. It is proposed to
                            make Liberia eligible for Lend-Lease aid,<note n="14" xml:id="d435fn14">For correspondence on this subject, see <ref target="#pg_404">pp.
                                    404</ref> ff.</note> which would doubtless cover the needs of
                            the frontier force as described by you. <pb facs="0380" n="368" xml:id="pg_368"/> War Department is planning to undertake
                            preliminary road construction to the extent of about $200,000, under the
                            credit, thus relieving Liberia of any immediate responsibility in
                            ordering materials.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>